Thermal  Power Plants  and Mines
Kostolac, a unit of Serbian power monopoly Elektroprivreda
Srbije JP, signed a contract for a $344.6 million loan, the
first phase of financing its upgrade, Beta  news agency  said.  Upgrades, which will take 30 months, are due to start in
the first half of 2012, Beta said, adding that the contract was
signed between Serbiaâ€™s Energy and Infrastructure Minister
Milutin Mrkonjic and Zhang Wanxue, the Chinese ambassador to
Serbia. Eighty-five percent of the funds will be soft loans from
 Export-Import Bank of China (EIBCZ) , its state export credit agency, it
